                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; reddish-brown; red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10788WaldaMuse">Walda Muse</persName>The
                        handwriting is identical to that of Walda Muse (cp. also the ruling pattern
                        and the ornamental bands). See Mss. MR-004, MR-009, MR-014b, MR-023, MR-016,
                           AGM-009.<date>Second half of the 19th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ቅ for ቅዱስ</item>
                           <item>ሰአ for ሰአል</item>
                           <item>ሰ for ሰላም</item>
                           <item>ይዲ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን</item>
                           <item>ይሕ for ይቤ፡ ሕዝብ</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the Trinitarian formula in the incipit
                           page of the text (fol. 3r); incipit of the subsections; elements of the
                           punctuation signs, elements of Ethiopic numerals;</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>: Simple ornamental band.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#52r">52r</locus>: Simple ornamental band.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc>: Unclear note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: አባቴ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ዕቀብ…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> An appeal of Mazgaba Śǝllāse who wrote the note, to "his father"
                              Walda Māryām and Mazgaba Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified prayer.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ግነዩ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ወጸውኡ፡ ስሞ፡
                              ምዕመናን…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Probably written in the same hand as that of Additio 1. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Unclear short note in the upper margin, probably in the
                           same hand as that of Additio 1, mentioning "7 righteous ones" (Ṣādǝqān):
                              <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.
 - Writing exercises: fols.
                           1-2.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
